OnSystemShellDredd

Target IP: 192.168.170.130

Scanning


Hmmm.... only two TCP ports on this machine: FTP and SSH. From the scan above, it shows anonymous login is allowed for the FTP application.

Enumeration

Port 21: FTP

There is a hidden directory called .hannah. This directory contains an SSH key for possibly hannah? I downloaded the SSH key to my local machine.

Exploitation


After downloading the SSH key to my machine, I changed the permission to 400. From the enumeration above, I know the SSH is located on port 61000. Then I logged in as hannah using the command ssh hannah@192.168.170.130 -i id_rsa -p 61000. Now we have a foothold on the machine.

Privilege Escalation


Running find / -perm -u=s 2>/dev/null shows an interesting binary called /usr/bin/cpulimit. I was able to gain a root shell by leveraging this binary with the command ./cpulimit -l 100 -f -- /bin/sh -p. And now I am root.

Flags


The local.txt is located in the same directory when we gain a foothold.


The proof.txt once I used cpulimit to elevate my privileges to root.
